0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When multiple requests are waiting to be sent, they are dispatched in the order they were originally submitted.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Testing dispatch order requires multiple concurrent callers racing in a real event loop. A Unit mock of sequential calls won't expose an off-by-one queue bug (e.g., LIFO vs FIFO). The test must submit requests concurrently, trigger quota exhaustion to force queueing, and verify the dispatch (and retry) order matches submission order. This requires Integration.","test_description":"Mock HTTP with a spy that records call timestamps and enforces quota (e.g., 1 call per 50ms window). Submit 3 async requests in rapid succession: await Promise.all([client.call('/a'), client.call('/b'), client.call('/c')]) at t=0. All three hit quota and are queued. As time advances and quota refreshes, assert HTTP spy records calls in order [/a, /b, /c], not [/b, /a, /c] or any other permutation. Verify retries also respect submission order.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.85,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13438,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13438},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7bd56289-e77c-4a90-a19e-319d792b1497","uuid":"fb89efc1-3029-4aed-bdad-9322ef9a3089"}
